## Project conventions — read first

Before answering or editing code, read these files in `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/`:

- `coding-conventions.md` — language style and idioms
- `architecture.md` — DDD layering rules
- `testing.md` — what / where / how to test
- `security.md` — security posture and constraints

They are authoritative — if anything here conflicts with them, they win.

## Source layout

```
src/application/      Use cases, services, orchestration
src/domain/           Pure business logic (entities, value objects, interfaces)
src/infrastructure/   DB, network, drivers, external adapters
src/presentation/     Entry points (HTTP routers, CLI, ISRs)
tests/{unit,integration,e2e,performance}
```

Empty directories are prefixed with `_` until they receive their first file.

